        rationale: "An unconscious patient with severe hypoglycemia (38 mg/dL) requires glucagon administration via IM injection or nasal spray. NEVER give oral carbohydrates (juice, glucose tablets) to an unconscious patient — the risk of aspiration is extremely high. Glucagon stimulates hepatic glycogenolysis, releasing stored glucose and rapidly raising blood sugar within 10-15 minutes. Once the patient regains consciousness, oral carbohydrates should be given to replenish glycogen stores. Emergency services should also be contacted."
